&gt;  I'm just wrapping up my conversion of the ColdC Reference Manual into 
&gt;Word2k format (Word97 shares the same format).  I've added headings, 
&gt;footnotes where appropriate, cleaned up the spelling and grammar, tried 
&gt;to standardized usage of italics/bold and set the document up to be 
&gt;printed so that it could be then bound double-sided to save space/paper, 
&gt;etc. 
&gt;   
&gt;  I've run into three problems:
&gt;
&gt;  The missing section on Textdump Structure
&gt;  The missing section of Native Method Reference
&gt;  and unless I'm missing something, buf_to_str and buf_to_strings share 
&gt;the exact same description (which I believe, belongs to buf_to_strings)
&gt;
&gt;  I'm more than happy to share what I've completed with anyone 
&gt;interested, or even have the doc posted on the cold.org site if that's a 
&gt;reasonable thing to do.
